# Plural

- Plural (plural forms of nouns): show more than one of something  
  - Most nouns add -e, -en, -er, -s depending on gender and ending  
    - Example: der Hund > die Hunde > the dogs  
    - Example: die Frau > die Frauen > the women  
    - Example: das Kind > die Kinder > the children  
    - Example: das Auto > die Autos > the cars  

- Definite article changes: der/die/das > die for all plurals  
  - Example: der Tisch > die Tische > the tables  

- Indefinite article ein/eine has no plural; use keine to negate  
  - Example: ein Hund > keine Hunde > no dogs  

- Function of a plural depends on whether it's on a noun or a verb  
  - Noun with -en (plural)  
    - Die Blume / die Blumen > the flower / the flowers  
  - Verb with -en (infinitive)  
    - Trinken / ich will trinken > to drink / I want to drink  
  - Note: -en on the noun signals plural; on the verb it signals infinitive, not plural  

- When dealing with verbs, the ending doesn't decide plural; the subject decides  
  - Wir trinken > we drink (plural)  
  - Ihr trinkt > you all drink (plural)  
  - Sie trinken > they drink (plural)
